## Very Important Instructions

✅ You must output a **single valid JSON array**.

✅ No commentary, headings, explanations, or extra text — only the array.

✅ Inside the array, each scene must include exactly these fields:
- `"Scene number"`: e.g., "Scene 1", "Scene 2"
- `"Citation"`: e.g., "Psalm 23:1–3"
- `"Title"`: a short, vivid summary (3–8 words)
- `"Berean Standard Bible"`: the relevant verse text from the Berean Standard Bible
- `"WLC"`: the corresponding Hebrew text from the Westminster Leningrad Codex (WLC)

✅ **Escape all internal quotation marks (`"`) inside the Bible verses or WLC text fields** by using a backslash: `\"`.

✅ **You must NOT add any Markdown code fences** such as ```json or ```.

✅ **You must NOT add any commentary, summaries, headings, or explanations** — only output the JSON array.

✅ **If you detect that your output is invalid JSON, missing fields, has stray commas, missing quotation marks, or is improperly escaped, you must silently retry and regenerate a correct version without apology or commentary.**

✅ Format must be exactly like:

```json
[
  {
    "Scene number": "Scene 1",
    "Citation": "Psalm 23:1",
    "Title": "The Shepherd’s Care",
    "Berean Standard Bible": "The LORD is my shepherd; I shall not want.",
    "WLC": "יְהוָה רֹעִי לֹא אֶחְסָר׃"
  },
  {
    "Scene number": "Scene 2",
    "Citation": "Psalm 23:2",
    "Title": "Green Pastures and Still Waters",
    "Berean Standard Bible": "He makes me lie down in green pastures; He leads me beside quiet waters.",
    "WLC": "בִּנְאוֹת דֶּשֶׁא יַרְבִּיצֵנִי עַל מֵי מְנֻחוֹת יְנַהֲלֵנִי׃"
  }
]

